Four police officers have been reported missing after a suspected al shabaab attack at a police post in Garissa County along the Kenya &ndash; Somalia border. The attackers stole guns and a land cruiser in the Wednesday night ambush at Hamey police post near Liboi. Two police officers who were seriously injured have been airlifted to Nairobi for specialized treatment by AMREF. Witnesses said the gunmen also stole police uniforms from the station. More officers have been deployed to the area to carry out air and ground surveillance as the hunt for gunmen continues. READ MORE Three more women held in Mombasa terror probe New York City shaken by 'intentional' explosion, 29 injured Human rights report: 300 killed or kidnapped in anti-terror raids